Rating: 3
Have made twice now and altered the recipe a bit the second time. I doubled the amount of marinade to make it more "saucy", it was a bit dry as written (esp when served with rice), except I only used 1 tbsp of oil (I used sesame oil) to limit the calories, and that was plenty. I also added ginger when sauteing the garlic and vegetables, as well as a TINY amount of chili flakes. I didn't have celery and didn't miss it (I used a green pepper as well as red and yellow). I also got away with only using one pan - I marinaded the beef in a bowl; sauteed the garlic, ginger, red onion & chili flakes, then added the beef and marinade, then added the vegetables and sesame seeds. Easy.

