Rating: 3
Very good and easy to make. I served it over basmati rice which was good. I added a can of bamboo shoots and a can of sliced water chestnuts and a few handfulls of frozen broccoli and glugged in some extra soy sauce to make sure there was enough liquid. I doubled the recipe and the leftovers were delicous. I only put in half of the sesame seeds since it sounded like too much. Make sure you cut the beef in small thin strips so not too chewy. I marinated the beef about 4 hours, try not to overcook the beef like I did.

